description.text: Welcome to this great 2 Bed/2 Bath Encino Condo with a large living room and dining area, hardwood like floors, and a modern kitchen with granite counter-tops, white cabinetry and a fabulous industrial sink plus refrigerator, stove, microwave, and dishwasher. The master suite includes a walk-in closet and dressing area, the second bedroom has dark hardwood flooring and a ceiling fan. Second bathroom with wainscoting, white tile shower and pedestal sink. Enjoy the amazing features of Central A/C, laundry on site, an exterior balcony, two tandem parking spots and an extra storage unit. Water, trash, gas and landscaping included, WOW! Go for a swim year-round in either of the heated Swimming pools and relax in the Jacuzzi. Only 0.4 miles from Ventura blvd. where you can enjoy many shops and restaurants. Close to Sherman Oaks, Studio City, Woodland Hills, Lake Balboa and only 5 miles from CSUN!

Situated in vibrant Encino, this beautiful one-bedroom, loft style condo offers an enviable setting with its proximity to shopping, restaurants, and easy access to freeways. The unit has modern bathrooms, a stylish kitchen and tile flooring. With its spacious layout, high ceilings, and generous closets it provides ample space and light. Enjoy the secluded 3rd floor location towards the back of the complex and private balcony overlooking courtyard. Condo community amenities include a pool, tennis courts, gym, and BBQ areas. Water and trash are included. The gated community offers private security for peace of mind, elevator for easy access and two tandem parking spots. A remarkable opportunity to experience the best of Encino living.

Welcome to Rancho El Mirador -an extraordinary Spanish-style luxury hacienda on a 3.5 acre estate, virtually unseen from Rancho, the Valley's most prestigious street. One of very few luxury residences created by acclaimed Early California architect Myron Hunt (Huntington Library, Rose Bowl, etc). Newly expanded/updated with amenities like no other: a tall mirador (look out tower), a real chapel with 1800's stained glass and organ, a large stage with 9' Steinway concert grand and custom acoustic ceiling, walls of glass doors opening to covered arched pergolas, multiple custom tiled courtyards with beautiful dining options. Chef's kitchen with La Cornue Cornufe range, La Marzocco espresso machine, two refrigerators, two sinks, opens to bougainvillea filled entertaining space with outdoor pizza oven and rotisserie bbq, a large outdoor covered bar with keg fridge, built in seating, swing, and fireplace. Artistically appointed furnishings include large scale art by CA artist Ray Turner, and a 17' enameled masterpiece in the dining room. Walk up the beautifully tiled curved stairs to 4 en-suite view bedrooms, with the primary bedroom surrounded by walls of glass doors spanning the width of the home that to fold open to enjoy the hillside breeze and cacophony of bird song. Step down the spiral stair to large pool/spa and take a hike on lighted, paved walking paths throughout to experience 80+ California oaks, native plantings, curated gardens, a lighted soccer pitch with tiered seating, a bocce ball court, a lighted pickle ball court with basketball hoops, a large pool/spa, a 900 sq ft gym complete with Pilates reformer, Cadillac reformer, Tonal machine, treadmill, boxing bag and much more. Very large circular cobblestone motor court has a tiled fountain and seating areas with custom California tile artwork evoking Adamson Malibu tile. Walk down the long cobblestone driveway canopied by old Oaks to exit the fully fenced and gated estate for a five minute stroll to famous Ventura Blvd, filled with restaurants and shopping. Experience LA's Hollywood Bowl summer concert lineup: 12 miles. Drive to Beverly Hills: 14 miles. Fly private from Van Nuys Airport: 6 miles. LA and Malibu beaches nearby. The mood and vibe is of the iconic Hotel California; an artistic and artful creation that only a few may experience. Rental includes daily turndown service and housekeeping, plus an estate manager/groundskeeper for questions and support. Whole home has water filtration system. Book your summer camp at Rancho El Mirador .

Situated in the heart Encino sits this lovely 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom luxury condo. Stepping through the double doors you will notice the exquisite attention to detail. From the laminate flooring to all new recessed lighting, this semi open concept floorpan will suit all of your needs. Directly off of the living room sits a fully remodeled chefs kitchen, featuring quartz countertops, new cabinetry and stainless steal appliances. Both of the oversized bedrooms flood with natural light and feature ample closet space. The primary bedroom features a large walk in closet and custom ensuite bathroom. Both of the bathrooms feature custom stone and tile work throughout. The home also features a generous sized balcony. This well maintained elevator building also features a large swimming pool for all your recreational needs. This home also features 2 car parking. In close proximity to Ventura blvd, the 101 and 405 freeways. This home can be leased furnished or unfurnished and is available for short or long term lease.

The latest gem in the Encino landscape is ready to rent. Enter the privately gated compound via the 'Ferris Bueller garage' or down the floating stairway over the Koi pond to the 10ft pivot entry door as unobstructed 180 degree views await. The latest multi million dollar development by Racing Green Group does not disappoint. Entering the main house you are met with incredible cedar and oak detailing set against the backdrop of some of the best views of the Encino Hills. Here you will find open plan living, dining and kitchen areas, as well as the Premier suite, two generous guest bedrooms, and maids rooms, all en suite, as well as a family/media room pre-wired with surround sound audio. The kitchen features hand crafted rift sawn white oak paneling set against elephant grey base cabinetry and delivers a stunning catering experience with 36 sink, Thermador and Wolf appliances, two dishwashers, and a separate Butlers kitchen and large walk in pantry. The premier bedroom boasting almost 1, 000sf, continues to impress with large oak paneled walk in wardrobe, coffee station and beverage center, as well as a beautiful bathroom suite with some of the best views in the house. Descending to the lower ground floor the entertainment levels step up to reveal an expansive bar and games room, complete with TV wall, large private gym suite and two other en suite guest bedrooms which could also work as private office spaces. Outside the magic continues with panoramic views from the infinity pool, large Brazilian Ipe deck, large enough to deliver several outdoor dining and seating moments, as well as several large, flat grassy areas, and a steel framed Gazebo, all set amongst the back drop of unparalleled views.

This luxury home has been carefully constructed on three levels and features its own elevator in order to effortlessly access the exquisite details in architecture and design found throughout this palatial 7 bedroom and 8 bathroom estate with almost 11, 000 square feet of living space. This property perfectly embodies modern elegance as it was tastefully designed with features such as a custom-built focal point chandelier fixture, impeccable quality quartz stone imported from Italy, beautiful hardwood and stone floors, and multiple custom fireplaces. The kitchen is adorned with a large entertainment island, quartz countertops and equipped with the finest Wolf and Viking appliances. Additionally, this property features a secondary service kitchen and a butler's pantry fit for any top chef. The living spaces feature vaulted ceilings that have been tastefully appointed to entertain the most significant events yet remain warm and inviting enough for daily enjoyment. The formal dining room is a designated space for dining with exquisite, unmatched details. In addition to the six gorgeous ensuite bedrooms elegantly placed throughout the home, there is a primary suite fit for royalty. This suite boasts an imported fireplace, a spa-like bathroom, spacious dual walk-in closets with custom built-ins, and a large spacious balcony to take in the views. Additional amenities of this home include recessed lighting, a laundry room equipped with appliances, a gym with equipment included, built-in cabinetry, a four car garage with showroom floors, and a utility room designed to centralize all audio and video, including smart features through DoorBird. With grounds over 28, 000 square feet, you have ample space for entertaining and the benefit from the ultra-private compound grounds with low maintenance yards, artificial turf, and mature landscape. This estate is truly one-of-a-kind and deserves a visit to experience its majesty.

With its prime location, unparalleled craftsmanship, and luxurious features, this high-end home in Encino is the epitome of luxury living, offering an extraordinary lifestyle that surpasses all expectations.
